{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Tools and Techniques","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>To use your combat magic effectively, you rely on a collection of tools and techniques. Cross off one; you'll need the rest.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Consumables</strong>. You need certain supplies -- powders, oils, etc. -- on hand, some will be used up each cast. If you don't have them, take 1-harm ignore-armour when you cast.</li>\n<li><strong>Foci</strong>. You need wands, staves, and other obvious props to focus. If you don't have what you need, your combat magic does 1 less harm.</li>\n<li><strong>Gestures</strong>. You need to wave your hands around to use combat magic. If you're restrained, take -1 ongoing for combat magic.</li>\n<li><strong>Incantations</strong>. You must speak in an arcane language to control your magic. If you use combat magic without speaking,&nbsp;<strong>act under pressure</strong> to avoid scrambling your thoughts.</li>\n</ul>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3DUWBcvFlA5fw8NX"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Could've Been Worse","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you miss a <strong>use magic</strong> roll you can choose one of the following options instead of losing control of the magic:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fizzle: </strong>The preparations and materials for the spell are ruined. You&rsquo;ll have to start over from scratch with the prep time doubled.</li>\n<li><strong>This Is Gonna Suck: </strong>The effect happens, but you trigger all of the listed glitches but one. You pick the one you avoid.</li>\n</ul>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9gPQju1WNtJI4Tt2"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Shield Spell","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you&nbsp;<strong>protect someone</strong>, gain 2-armour against any harm that is transferred to you. This doesn't stack with your other armour, if any.</p>","rating":"cool"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AyD5ythZBwhnqiF3"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Go Big or Go Home","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>&nbsp;When you must <strong>use magic</strong> as a requirement for Big Magic, take +1 ongoing to those use magic rolls.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"G98XTV9AD4PCwwad"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Arcane Reputation","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>Pick three big organizations or groups in the supernatural community, which can include some of the more sociable types of monsters. They&rsquo;ve heard of you and respect your power. With affected humans, take +1 forward when you <strong>manipulate</strong> them. You may <strong>manipulate</strong> affected monsters as if they were human, with no bonus.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IQP4CpngMniPcyCg"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Enchanted Clothing","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>Pick an article of every-day clothing&ndash;it&rsquo;s enchanted without any change in appearance. Take -1 harm from any source that tries to get at you through the garment.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Q60zqjgesLbXXI7R"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Practitioner","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>Choose two effects available under&nbsp;<strong>use magic</strong>. Take +1 to <strong>use magic</strong> whenever you choose one of those effects.</p>","rating":"weird"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dTdM79dG6kW1wkUu"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Forensic Divination","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you successfully&nbsp;<strong>investigate a mystery</strong>, you may ask \"What magic was done here?\" as a free extra question.</p>","rating":"sharp"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hilmlZqErKeeGLuD"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Not My Fault","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>+1 to <strong>act under pressure</strong> when you are dealing with the consequences of your own spell- casting.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"im914wqN0iAfPLBm"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Third Eye","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>When you&nbsp;<strong>read a bad situation</strong>, you can&nbsp;<strong>open up your third eye</strong> for a moment to take in extra information. Take +1 hold on any result of 7 or more, plus you can see invisible things. On a miss, you may still get 1 hold, but you're exposed to supernatural danger. Unfiltered hidden reality is rough on the mind!</p>","rating":"sharp"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jgXYqqnxChUvWHki"}
{"name":"[Spell-Slinger] Advanced Arcane Training","permission":{"default":0,"eveotneFDj7m7tAm":3},"type":"move","data":{"description":"<p>If you have two of your three Tools and Techniques at the ready, you may ignore the third one.</p>","rating":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jtXw4ft8ytEvgncY"}
